  "prompt": "What is the difference between Windows and Linux?",
  "response": "Here are key differences between Windows and Linux:\n\n1. Operating System Characteristics\n- Windows: Proprietary, developed by Microsoft\n- Linux: Open-source, developed by community\n\n2. Cost\n- Windows: Paid commercial operating system\n- Linux: Mostly free\n\n3. User Interface\n- Windows: More user-friendly, graphical interface\n- Linux: Variety of interfaces, can be more technical\n\n4. Software Compatibility\n- Windows: Wider commercial software support\n- Linux: More limited commercial software, strong open-source alternatives\n\n5. Security\n- Windows: More targeted by malware, requires antivirus\n- Linux: Generally more secure, fewer viruses\n\n6. Customization\n- Windows: Limited customization options\n- Linux: Highly customizable, multiple distributions\n\n7. System Resources\n- Windows: Typically requires more system resources\n- Linux: Generally lighter, can run on older hardware\n\n8. Command Line\n- Windows: Less powerful command prompt\n- Linux: Robust terminal with extensive capabilities\n\n9. Updates\n- Windows: Mandatory, often frequent and disruptive\n- Linux: Optional, less intrusive\n\n10. Target Users\n- Windows: Home and business users\n- Linux: Developers, tech enthusiasts, servers\n\nEach has strengths depending on specific user needs.",
